A Análise Social é a principal revista portuguesa em ciências sociais e na área dos estudos sobre Portugal. Durante mais de meio século, a revista manteve o seu cariz inovador devido à capacidade para atrair trabalhos que resultam de investigação de topo, tanto teórica como empiricamente, e à originalidade e importância dos temas abordados.

A Análise Social é uma revista multidisciplinar, especializada nas áreas da Sociologia, da História, da Antropologia, da Ciência Política e da Psicologia Social. Dá prioridade à publicação de artigos que em cada uma destas áreas:

Apresentem investigação empírica baseada em formulações e modelos teóricos;
Desenvolvam novos métodos de análise e investigação;
Usem conceitos heurísticos para a interpretação da realidade;
Contenham implicações teóricas da investigação empírica;
Contribuam para o desenvolvimento de perspectivas comparadas sobre os temas estudados.

Le CASD est un groupement d’intérêt public rassemblant l’État représenté par INSEE, le GENES, le CNRS, l’École polytechnique et HEC Paris créé par arrêté interministériel du 29 décembre 2018.
Le GIP, à vocation industrielle et commerciale, a pour objet principal d’organiser et de mettre en œuvre des services d’accès sécurisé pour les données confidentielles à des fins non lucratives de recherche, d’étude, d’évaluation ou d’innovation, activités qualifiées de « services à la recherche », principalement publiques. Il a également pour mission de valoriser la technologie développée pour sécuriser l’accès aux données dans le secteur privé.
Le groupement est chargé dans le cadre de ses missions de service à la recherche :

    de mettre en œuvre des services sécurisés d’accès aux données confidentielles ;
    de participer aux opérations d’appariement, d’anonymisation de données et à la constitution de bases de données ;
    de participer à la documentation et à l’archivage des données confidentielles.
A l’interface entre les producteurs déposants de données et leurs utilisateurs, le CASD propose un équipement garantissant un accès hautement sécurisé aux données qui lui sont confiées.
    participer aux séances du Comité du secret statistique et collaborer avec son secrétariat ;
    d’animer la communauté d’utilisateurs autour des données confidentielles ;
    de concourir à la certification des résultats de la recherche s’appuyant sur des données confidentielles ;
    de participer au développement de l’accès aux données confidentielles au niveau national, au niveau européen et au niveau international en lien avec les autres dispositifs de mise à disposition de données ;

EWASH & TI est une revue scientifique électronique œuvrant dans la publication des travaux scientifiques nationaux et internationaux en relation avec les trois grands panels de thématiques :
(1) - Sciences appliquées à l’Eau et à l’Environnement ;
(2) - Impacts Environnementaux Globaux et Santé Publique ;
(3) - Intelligence Territoriale.
EWASH & TI est une publication internationale, évaluée par les pairs et à accès libre. Elle vise la promotion des travaux de recherches dans les domaines spécifiés ci-dessus, en les soumettant à une double évaluation par un comité de lecture constitué d’experts du domaine. Son édition est trimestrielle. EWASH & TI est un journal scientifique pluridisciplinaire au service de la recherche scientifique et du développement durable.
EWASH & Ti Journal est fondé en 2016 par Hinde CHERKAOUI DEKKAKI, Professeur à la Faculté des Sciences et Techniques d’Al Hoceima, Université Abdelmalek Essaadi , Maroc.

The GEO Knowledge Hub is a central cloud-based digital library providing access to Earth Observations based applications developed by the GEO Work Programme Activities and other authoritative sources of EO based open applications.

The scope of the GEO Knowledge Hub is to promote the replicability and re-usability of EO based applications by sharing with the end user all the Knowledge Resources essential to fully understand and re-use them. All knowledge resources of a registered EO application, are openly shared, curated and organized into a Knowledge Package, including: 

1. Research papers and reports describing methods and results;
2. Software algorithms and cloud computing resources used for processing;
3. In situ and satellite imagery data used;
4. Results for verification.

The International Journal of Applied Operational Research (IJAOR) publishes high quality, original papers that contribute to the field of operational research (OR) and its related issues. Operational research (OR) is an analytical method of problem-solving and decision-making that is useful in the management of organizations in which problems are broken down into basic components and then solved in a number of definitive and predetermined steps through applying mathematical analyses. A number of analytical methods that are commonly used in OR include mathematical logic, simulation, network analysis, and so forth. We are delighted to announce that the journal is going to accept articles in one of the following realms and categories:
-Decision theory and analysis;
-Data Envelopment Analysis;
-Probabilistic and stochastic models;
-Operational research techniques in finance and marketing;
-Manufacturing and operations theory and practice;
-Operational models in services;
-Logistics and OR models and techniques;
-Applications of operational research techniques;
-Military and operational research models;
-Operational research in public sector organizations;
-Statistics modeling;
-OR for investment strategy;
-OR in ecology;
-OR and multiple criteria decision making.
-OR in urban planning.
-OR in inventory control;
-OR in economics;
-OR in management;
-OR and telecommunication and networking;
-Optimization in operations research;
-OR in transportation;
-Fuzzy sets and systems;
-Discrete optimization;
-Production inventory;
-Heuristic Method;
-Stochastic process;
-Integer programming; and
-Sequencing and scheduling.

IJTTHL offers a regular source of practical information for legal practitioners and researchers dealing with  Tourism, Travel and Hospitality Law on a day-to-day basis, principally dealing with European law and the laws of other European, American and Asian countries. 
With pre-prints and two issues per year, IJTTHL offers readers the following: 
	-  Analytical articles on topics of current importance written by experts in the field;  
	-  Current Comment on specific areas of tourism, travel and hospitality law;  
	-  In Parliament section summarising the critical legislative developments; 
	-  Reviews of the latest publications.

The Ecotoxicology Database contains – for substances listed in the NORMAN Substance Database – experimental endpoints from ecotox tests as well as quality targets from different regulatory contexts.

The term Lowest PNECs refers to quality targets which are suggested by experts for prioritisation purposes. They are obtained experimentally or predicted by QSAR models. The Ecotoxicology Database provides a transparent tool to help experts in:

the identification of the reliable ecotoxicity studies, based on the CRED (Criteria for Reporting and Evaluating ecotoxicity Data) classification system;
the online derivation of Quality Targets for each matrix and regulatory framework based on selected ‘reliable’ ecotoxicity studies, using a built-in software tool implementing the requirements of the EC guidelines;
the compilation of all existing Quality Targets from different regulatory frameworks;
the final selection of the Lowest PNEC value for substance prioritisation purposes, agreed upon as a result of Europe-wide expert consultations.

The catalogue represents an organized collection point for spatial data, web map services, maps or even non geographic datasets produced by the CNR-ISMAR in multidisciplinary fields (geophysics, geology, biology, carthography, etc).
It is implemented using the free open source software GeoNetwork for the management of spatially referenced resources. It enables the exchange of information about:
• The presence of data in the geographical database;
• The access mode and use of geographic data;
• The usability of data in specific application contexts;
• The systems and procedures used for the production of data;
• The points of contact.
